values:
"I'm reaching further than I ever have before, leaving all who broke your heart upon the shore.&nbsp; I may be some sort of&nbsp;crazy, we may be some sort of&nbsp;crazy, but I swear on everything I have and more."&nbsp; Blue October, Sound of pulling Heaven Down.

I thought this was a weird song, like the rest of the album's lyrics however, I really like this song a lot.&nbsp; It makes you think about liking someone.....and then reaching further to that whole love thing.&nbsp; If you really love someone then you can start to leave hurt behind you.&nbsp; And some of the things you do for each other seem crazy but its worth it.....cuz it is for each other.&nbsp;&nbsp;

When I look at happy couples I think wow that is really cool, when they just click other couples seem happy but you can just tell something is missing and you know they aren't over the past, cuz it is not meant to be.&nbsp;&nbsp;Yet some times we force ourselves to make the ideal situation give us butterflies.&nbsp;&nbsp;

I see my friends who are married and engaged and I think wow...there are worse things than being single....about a few of them.&nbsp; And others I know its right for them and it really makes me believe there is some one out there for all of us.&nbsp; But before we get to that place we have to be willing to make ourselves be at that level...you know above, that and more place.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Its the being happy in just doing nothing with that person, the everyday life stuff.&nbsp;

Katie came over and her favorite game is Taboo, just like mine.&nbsp; Matt did not want to be social but I kinda made him come down stairs I needed a partner.&nbsp; Well we kicked ass, by 20 points.&nbsp; We really are a great team when we don't fight.&nbsp; And as strange as it sounds we usually win if we work together and not against each other.&nbsp; It is actually kinda fun.&nbsp; And I think it helped that I mentioned to Colin he had to take personal responsibility today.&nbsp; (I might baby that boy (C), but that doesn't mean I tell him he is never wrong.....he is a lot.&nbsp; And the trouble he is intoday is a perfect example of it.....missing a court date is no one's fault but your own.)

Yeah so I like the whole getting along thing maybe I will mention that to him.&nbsp; He is a lot more fun when he is sober to.&nbsp; I hate mean drunks.&nbsp; Like last night cutting himself and pouring salt on it so the pain could be weakness leaving the body.&nbsp; Whatever that means, its a marine thing.&nbsp; Then I had to cover for him at work this evening cuz he was still hung over.&nbsp; I hate addiction.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Although if I wanted to get way into it, I would go off on my rant about the amount of scape goating we do to depression and addiction.........lack of creativity in activities is not an excuse for doing drugs, emotional issues need to be dealt with cuz you can't numb them forever, and drugs just don't make you cool!&nbsp; Okay we are out of high school.&nbsp; Cool kids say no...usually.&nbsp; Okay done with the rant.&nbsp;&nbsp;

I had a job interview with Target and I think I got the job.....I just have to pass the drug test which should not have been a problem.&nbsp; Its a job atleast.&nbsp; Which is more to do than work with Matt.&nbsp;

I am sitting in my online class and pointed out a huge mistake, and logically speaking it should have been caught.&nbsp; It pisses me off that I had to find it.&nbsp; But I guess it just goes along with my usual days lately.&nbsp;&nbsp;
And I ask myself why I question and second guess myself when I think everyone else around me is wrong...actually I know they are wrong.&nbsp;&nbsp;

I saw Colin again today nothing special about that, spent $ i do not have getting the oil changed on his&nbsp;truck and putting gass in his truck.&nbsp; I figured he needed it worse than I do.&nbsp; This just majorly cuts into my alcohol fund which sucks cuz well I want to numb my feelings.&nbsp; I tried jogging till I couldn't breath and was exhausted, well that hurt my ankle.&nbsp; So I guess it doesn't numb anything.&nbsp; Anyhow....he thinks his brother might come home tonight...i doubt it.&nbsp;&nbsp;
I invited him so see a movie and I think things are getting back to normal, but I am not sure.&nbsp; I can't be honset with my feelings cuz I am to shaken into thinking he will never feel the same.&nbsp; And my heart has been broken way way to many times.&nbsp; But I will admit I miss the way he makes me smile.&nbsp; But I refuse to be the stupid girl that gives till it hurts...oh wait a little to late for that.&nbsp;&nbsp;
Yeah I figured Da Vinci Code was still out so he might want to go see it.....haven't heard back, but maybe C ame home after all.&nbsp; He asked if I had seen Munich...he has it at home....i said I wanted to.&nbsp; Then I said the DaVinci Code wasn't a date....he found that laughable.&nbsp; Fuck it!
I think it is time to move out of this place.&nbsp; I don't care if it is walking out on my feelings.&nbsp; I don't want to hurt anymore.&nbsp; I am sooooo having difficulty blocking out the pain.&nbsp;&nbsp;
But do I need to...maybe I should have my exit plan in place and say by the way I love you but should I walk away?
